.TH VILISTEXTUM 1 "11 March 2003"
.SH NAME
vilistextum \- html to ascii converter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vilistextum
[options] [inputfile |-]
[outputfile | -]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX  vilistextum  ""  "\fLvilistextum\fP \(em html to ascii converter"
.B vilistextum
is a html to ascii converter specifically programmed to get the
best out of incorrect html.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
\fB\inputfile,- resp. outputfile,-\fR
Replace inputfile with '-' for reading from standard input, likewise
outputfile with '-' for writing to standard output.
.TP
\fB\--version\fR
Report version number and release date.
.TP
\fB\-h, --help\fR
Print a list of the command line options.
.TP
\fB\-c, --convert-tags
Some of the tags will be converted to special characters.

.TP
\fB\-p, --palm
Output text more suitable for reading on a PDA.

.TP
\fB\-w, --width NUMBER
Maximum line width.
.TP
\fB\-m, --dont-convert-characters
Don't convert the entities from windows1252 (&#128-&#159 and
their proper entity names)

.TP
\fB\-s, --shrink-lines [NUMBER]
If there are more than NUMBER empty lines, output only <NUMBER>.
Default: 1.
.TP
\fB\-l, --links
Numbers the links in the document and creates footnotes of each
link at the end of the file.
.TP
\fB\-t, --no-title
Don't output title
.TP
\fB\-e, --errorlevel NUMBER
Increase level of verbosity for error messages 
(0: No error messages).

.TP
\fB\-i, --defimage STRING
IMG tags without alt attribute are output as [STRING].
.TP
\fB\-r, --remove-empty-alt
If there is an empty ALT attribute in a IMG tag 
(eg <IMG href="..." alt="">), don't output '[]'.
.TP
\fB\-n, --no-image
Don't output [Image] for IMG tags that have no ALT attribute
.TP
\fB\-a, --no-alt
Don't output anything for IMG tags even if they have an ALT
attribute.
Implies \fB\--no-image.

.SH MULTIBYTE OPTIONS (Only available if compiled with multibyte support)
.TP
\fB\--charset DEFAULTCHARSET
If the HTML document doesn't provide a character set in the
meta tags, use DEFAULTCHARSET.
.TP
\fB\--translit
Use the //TRANSLIT feature of libiconv.
Consult the iconv manual for details.
.TP
\fB\--output-utf-8
Character set of output file is UTF8.


.SH LIMITATIONS
The rendering of tables is not very good.

The handling of OL is incomplete. The program treats it as UL
and more than 10 nested lists confuse it.

Text is never justified.

